{ Welcome, dear chess players, to the 15-minutes video! } 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 ( 3... Nf6 4. O-O Bc5 5. Nxe5 $1 Nxe4 ( 5... Nxe5 6. d4 a6 7. Be2 $16 ) 6. Qe2 Nxe5 7. d4 $1 Be7 8. dxe5 Nc5 9. Bc4 $16 { [%csl Rd7,Ge5][%cal Gf1d1,Gb1c3] } ) ( 3... Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d4 exd4 6. e5 Nd5 7. O-O Be7 $1 ( 7... O-O $2 8. cxd4 Be7 9. Qb3 Nb6 10. d5 $16 ) 8. a4 $5 { Best try to fight for an advantage. } ( 8. cxd4 d6 $11 ) 8... a6 9. Bc4 Nb6 10. Bb3 d5 ( 10... O-O $4 11. a5 $18 ) 11. exd6 Qxd6 12. a5 Nd5 13. Nxd4 $14 { Black misses a tempo to be completely fine. } ) 4. Ba4 Nf6 ( 4... Bc5 5. c3 Nge7 $5 { New idea. } 6. O-O Ng6 7. d4 Ba7 8. Bxc6 $5 dxc6 9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. dxe5 { Not so easy to play for Black. For example: } 10... Qe7 ( 10... O-O 11. Qxd8 Rxd8 12. Nd2 $14 { [%cal Gf1e1,Gd2f1,Gc1e3] We will continue with Re1-Nf1-Be3. } ) 11. Qf3 Qxe5 12. Bf4 Qe7 13. Qg3 $36 { [%csl Rc7,Rg7][%cal Gg3g7,Gf4c7] } ) 5. O-O b5 ( 5... Bc5 $5 6. c3 b5 ( 6... O-O $5 7. d4 Ba7 { New idea. } 8. Bg5 h6 ( 8... exd4 9. e5 $36 ) 9. Bh4 exd4 10. Re1 $1 { [%cal Ge4e5,Rf6e4] Our idea is that when we will play e5, Black will not have Ne4. } ) 7. Bc2 d5 $1 { It's a very concrete line; we need to know what to do. } ( 7... d6 { [%csl Gc2] Not so good because our bishop is already on c2. } 8. d4 Bb6 9. a4 $14 { We have an improved version of the main Arkhangelsk because of Bc2. } ) 8. a4 dxe4 9. axb5 { Black has two continuations: Bg4 and exf3. } 9... Bg4 ( 9... exf3 10. Qxf3 { Black needs to find many only moves to stay in the game. } ) 10. bxc6 exf3 11. gxf3 Bh3 12. Re1 O-O 13. Ra5 $1 Qd6 14. b4 Bxf2+ $1 15. Kxf2 e4 16. Kg1 { This is only the start of a very interesting and entertaining position. } ) 6. Bb3 Bc5 ( 6... Bb7 7. d3 Bc5 8. a4 O-O ( 8... d6 9. Nc3 b4 10. Ne2 O-O ( 10... h6 11. Ng3 $14 ) 11. Bg5 h6 12. Bh4 $14 { [%csl Rb7][%cal Rg7g5,Gf3g5] Not so easy to play for Black because when he plays g5, we can sacrifice Nxg5. } ) 9. Bg5 h6 10. Bh4 Be7 ( 10... d6 $6 11. c3 $14 { [%cal Rg7g5,Gf3g5] When Black plays g5, we can sacrifice Nxg5. } ) ( 10... g5 11. Bg3 d6 12. Nbd2 $14 { [%cal Gf1e1,Gd2f1,Gf1e3] Our standard idea is Re1-Nf1-Ne3. } ) 11. axb5 axb5 12. Rxa8 Bxa8 13. Na3 $14 { We play against Black's bad bishop on a8. } ) 7. a4 Rb8 8. Nxe5 $5 Nxe5 9. d4 Bxd4 10. Qxd4 d6 11. Bf4 $5 c5 ( 11... O-O 12. axb5 axb5 13. Rd1 $1 { [%cal Rc7c5] We prevent c5. } ) 12. Qe3 c4 13. Ba2 { [%csl Ra2] } 13... O-O 14. Rd1 Re8 15. Nc3 b4 16. Ne2 { [%cal Gh2h3] h3 next, and Black should be well-prepared to equalize. } *

