, Black can no longer take on g5. } 19... Be3 20. Qe1 Qxg5 21. Rxf7 $18 ) 18. Bh4 $1 { [%cal Gc1f4] We prepare Qxf4. } 18... Be3 { only move. } 19. Bxf6 Bxc1 ( 19... Qxf6 $2 20. Qxe3 $18 ) 20. Bxd8 Bxb2 21. Rab1 Be5 22. Bh4 Rh7 23. Bg5 f3 24. Rxf3 Bxh2 25. Rxf7 $16 { Black has a very difficult endgame. } ) 17. Bxf7 Rg7 18. Be6 $1 { [%cal Rf6g4] The bishop should stay on the h3-c8 diagonal not to allow Ng4 ideas. } ( 18. Bb3 $6 Rh7 $1 19. f4 Ng4 $13 ) 18... Qe7 19. Bf5 Nd4 20. Nxd4 Bxd4 21. c3 Bc5 22. f4 exf4 23. Bxf6 ( 23. Qxf4 $1 Nh5 $11 ) 23... Qxf6 24. Qxf4 Qg5 25. Qf3 $14 { [%cal Gd3d4,Gg5h6] d4 next. Engine evaluates +0,60. We have three pieces for the pawn, and Black's king might be vulnerable. Also, Black's bishops are passive for the moment. It seems that Black's only move here is 25...Qh6! } *

