11. Bf4 $5 { This is a more positional option compared to 11.f4. Now, Black can choose between 00 and c5. If you think about it, now that we have on the board a sort of "Old Philidor structure", the best square for White's bishop is exactly f4. } ( 11. f4 { Leads to a very big theory, where Black needs to be precise, but he finally equalizes. } 11... Nc6 $11 ) *

